metadata.name: UPLOAD.EXE #228
metadata.description:
No death in the metaverse

Here then, a chance to right every wrong

metadata.name: Supernal Memories #312
metadata.description:
With its layered bursts of color, light, and shadow, Supernal Memories carries an underlying message of optimism through its harmony of seeming dualities – hard and soft, familiar and surprising, expression and introspection.

Each newly generated circle brings its own energy, creating layered groups of light that sometimes resemble phenomena like nebula, lightning sprites, and auras – ethereal whispers of something remembered. 

Supernal Memories is an invitation to observe the forms & feel of each piece without labeling their qualities, to contemplate the infinite possibilities of the universe, and to explore the depths of your imagination.


--

Created by Diego Pintos @DondiegoTez
Creative collaboration with Tender @tender_art

To get a high resolution file, add "&print=14000" to the end of the live URL / hash, using any resolution number that fits your needs. Press 's' to save the file when it is done loading.

Press 'p' to continue the animation for another variation.

100% code, made with p5.js
See license.md

metadata.name: Momentum #123
metadata.description:
In our new project, we explore the possibilities and tools of generative art. This time we were interested in the aesthetics of particles. When static turns into movement, and the predicted composition becomes spontaneous - the experiment continues.
This project was created with P5.js.
March 2023.
Press 'S' to save a PNG file.

metadata.name: Arrows Between Emotions #22
metadata.description:
The project “Arrows Between Emotions” was formed with a concern to present this transformation in an artist and code developer, making the logic appear through precise and well-defined forms, but that the stage was really of emotions through freer curves involving aligned with accentuated movements in directions of straight or oblique ascents and even in more circular or decadent processes that are part of the journey of the wheel of life of art and the artist.


The process of the work involved the construction of a background to receive the shapes and colors. I used an algorithm that generated a distribution of noise across the screen, with its coloring related to the shapes in the search for a pleasant composition. Then came the objective forms, setting the stage, finally, for the flow of emotions through the agglutinated and dispersed curves soaked in colors in a game of shadow and light, presenting the depth and movement of the creation process and the orientation to which it takes. all the strength of this walk.

Press 's' key in live mode to save in png.

@pixelflowart, May 2022

metadata.name: Threads of destiny #3
metadata.description:
"Threads of destiny" is an abstract artwork focusing on the composition and color of elements. Each thread consists of a sequence of shapes that are placed together in a harmonious rhythm, just like our world where each of us, while being unique, together form a larger design, each of the shapes, on the threads of destiny, with the help of each other, make a larger and harmonious composition. 

Various sizes and densities and more than 12 color palettes have been used.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.

metadata.name: Variations #107
metadata.description:
Thousands of rectangles of 8 different colors are positioned on the screen, each color following its own pattern.

By doing so they form shapes that are similar in some aspects, different in others, and together create a larger pattern. Sometimes these shapes are grouped to form another pattern at an intermediate level.

Each iteration, once minted, will also become part of a larger whole that is the generative piece.

SVG generated with JavaScript.

The SVG can be saved by pressing "s" on the full-screen view.
A PNG version can be exported by pressing "e" on the full-screen view.

By default the dimensions of the export are 3200×3200.
These dimensions can be changed by adding, for example, ?w=5000 to the full-screen page URL, where w is the desired width. Then press "e" to export at this size.

metadata.name: Ruins #124
metadata.description:
Ruins is a generative art project depicting abandoned ruins in a wild and beautiful environment where nature has taken over.

The soothing and hypnotic animation of the sky can be controlled by:
- clicking to pause or resume animation
- double-clicking to pause and display the initial image
- repeatedly pressing the + or - keys (or directional keys) to speed up or slow down the animation
- pressing f to increase the refresh rate to 60 FPS

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Clockwork Orange #17
metadata.description:
Title inspired from the 1971 dystopian crime film directed by Stanley Kubrick, based on Anthony Burgess's novel "A Clockwork Orange". The importance of evil as well as good in human nature is a fundamental theme of the movie.

The film looks into ideas of mind control and government manipulation, most clearly in the iconic scene in which Alex is restrained in a chair whilst his eyes are prised open and he is subjected to scenes of violence whilst listening to Beethoven.

The generative artwork is crafted with code in p5js and random Cellular Automata rules, with each iteration being unique and metaphorically representing the human eye.

Press "s" to save a printable, large PNG file (7x viewport size)

metadata.name: Digital Gardens #233
metadata.description:
Digital Gardens are places of magic and wonder, where you can connect with your inner nature and take a deep breath. Digital Gardens are a refuge from the world outside. A sanctuary for the mind, body, and soul. But they are also a place of play and exploration. It is a space where you can let your imagination run wild, creating and discovering new things.
Digital Gardens brings to life the minimalistic essence of Detegus’ art and the abstract and rational art of Alfredo Boaron.
The gardens are generated from a recursive function dividing the space at each iteration with a proportion that follows the Fibonacci succession and randomly stops after some iterations. At each recursion the canvas is divided into two pieces following the proportion of two consecutive Fibonacci numbers [1 to 144].
The minimalistic visual effect is then personalized by the palettes of 15 artists who embraced the invitation to give their personal contribution to the collection. The palette name and the author name is displayed in the features along with the Fibonacci numbers ratio, the colors number vs the total palette color number, the background color, the total number of rectangles and the depth level of recursion achieved by the algorithm.
Immerse yourself in this generative project, inspired by geometrism and abstract expressionism. 
Lose yourself in the beauty of a digital garden.

metadata.name: Flooded Harmony #8
metadata.description:
"Flooded Harmony", the second project of the Harmony collection. 
While we continue to produce new pieces from this Harmony collection, we strive to push the boundaries and show the different concepts in our new collections.
We're excited to introduce our new collections in near future that are totally different!

This piece features a dynamic color palette that seamlessly blends different shades to create a stunning visual experience. The day/night theme adds another layer of depth to the artwork, providing a glimpse into the duality of life. In addition to the theme and color palette, this NFT also offers different horizon heights, allowing you to see the artwork from various perspectives. 

Features:
- Different horizon heights
- Different Styles
- Day/Night Theme
- Multiple color palettes

-- Created in P5JS --
